            <pb n="6" facs="#f0001" />
            <div n="1">
                <p>The following communication was resolved upon at a<lb/>special meeting of the Colonial Society, convened to con-<lb/>gratulate that distinguished philosopher, the Baron von Hum-<lb/>boldt, upon his arrival in England, and to elect him an<lb/>honorary member of the society:&#x2014;</p>
                <floatingText>
                    <body>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline>
                                <hi rendition="#et">&#x201C;Colonial Society, Jan. 29.</hi>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>&#x201C;Sir,&#x2014;The committee of the Colonial Society, in con-<lb/>formity with a resolution unanimously adopted this day, beg<lb/>leave to express their gratification at your visit to this country<lb/>in the suite of your distinguished Sovereign.</p>
                        <p>&#x201C;Identified as the Colonial Society is with the extension<lb/>of civilisation and the development of the internal resources<lb/>of distant and imperfectly known foreign regions, the society<lb/>gladly avails itself of the present opportunity to tender its<lb/>respectful congratulations to a philosopher, whose invaluable<lb/>services in the cause of geographical discovery and humanity<lb/>are acknowledged and justly appreciated by all civilised na-<lb/>tions, for they have had for their special object the welfare<lb/>and advancement of mankind.</p>
                        <p>&#x201C;Understanding that your sojourn in England is neces-<lb/>sarily brief, the society is obliged to refrain from tendering<lb/>at present any other mark of their sincere esteem than that<lb/>of naming you an honorary member of their body, and in<lb/>doing so they would beg to offer their heartfelt wishes for<lb/>your continued health and happiness.</p>
                        <closer>&#x201C;By order of the committee,<lb/><hi rendition="#et">&#x201C;JULIUS LE SOUEF, Secretary.</hi>&#x201C;The Baron von Humboldt, &amp;c.&#x201D;</closer>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <lb/>
                <milestone unit="section" rendition="#hr"/>
                <lb/>
                <p>Baron von Humboldt returned the following answer :&#x2014;</p>
                <floatingText>
                    <body>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline><hi rendition="#et">&#x201C;Windsor Castle, le 30me Janvier, 1842.</hi></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>&#x201C;Monsieur,&#x2014;Dans la vie agiteé que nous menons pendant<lb/>le trop court sejour de mon Souverain en Angleterre, il ne me<lb/>reste que le regret de ne pas avoir un moment de libre pour<lb/>exprimer personellement au comité de l&#x2019;illustre &#x2018;Colonial<lb/>Society&#x2019; la vive reconnaissance dont je me sens pénétré. Je<lb/>vous supplie, Monsieur, de vouloir bien &#x00EA;tre l&#x2019;interprète de<lb/>mes sentimens respectueux. Rien ne pourrait &#x00EA;tre plus flat-<lb/>teur pour moi que l&#x2019;intér&#x00EA;t que mes faibles efforts ont pu<lb/>inspirer à une réunion dont les travaux tendent à un but si<lb/>noble et si bienfaisant pour l&#x2019;humanité.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <salute>&#x201C;Agréez, Monsieur, je vous supplie, l&#x2019;homage de la haute<lb/>considération avec laquelle j&#x2019;ai l&#x2019;honneur d&#x2019;&#x00EA;tre, Monsieur,<lb/>votre très humble et très obéissant serviteur,</salute>
                            <hi rendition="#et">&#x201C;Le Baron von HUMBOLDT.</hi>
                            &#x201C;M. Julius Le Souef, &amp;c.&#x201D;</closer>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
            </div>
            <lb/>
        </body>
